    "Dr. Peter S. Ruckman": "In such cases, stick with the infallible SOP of all Bible believers. Assume, from the start, that the Christian critics who are all dead-set on \u201cproving contradictions\u201d in student of the Scripture\u201d can begin (if he hasn\u2019t already begun \u201cto begin\u201d) to discard the comments of several hundred apostate, Laodicean commen tators who object to the \u201cdiscrepancies\u201d between the two \u201ccensuses\u201d of the people found in Ezra 2 and Nehemiah\n7. In such cases, stick with the infallible SOP of all Bible believers. Assume, from the start, that the Christian critics who are dead-set on \u201cproving contradictions\u201d in the AV are simply demon-obsessed egotists who wish to impress you with their \u201cbook larnin\u2019.\u201d (This is always the best rule to follow. It has never failed me one time in fifty-four years of dealing with more than 770,000 words in the Holy Bible [ AV, 1611].) The \u201cchargers\u201d are obviously like the one that \u201cserved up\u201d the head of John the Baptist to Mrs. Herod (Matt. 14:8; Mark 6:28): it is a large, hollowed-out dish (Heb.: kots ). The \u201cbasons\u201d are \u201ccovered goblets\u201d which would resemble any one of ten thousand German \u201csteins.\u201d [v_Neh_7_5] Unknown\n7. In such cases, stick with the infallible SOP of all Bible believers. Assume, from the start, that the Christian critics who are all dead-set on \u201cproving contradictions\u201d in student of the Scripture\u201d can begin (if he hasn\u2019t already begun \u201cto begin\u201d) to discard the comments of several hundred apostate, Laodicean commentators who object to the \u201cdiscrepancies\u201d between the two \u201ccensuses\u201d of the people found in Ezra 2 and Nehemiah\n7. In such cases, stick with the infallible SOP of all Bible believers. Assume, from the start, that the Christian critics who are dead-set on \u201cproving contradictions\u201d in the AV are simply demon-obsessed egotists who wish to impress you with their \u201cbook larnin\u2019.\u201d (This is always the best rule to follow. It has never failed me one time in fifty-four years of dealing with more than 770,000 words in the Holy Bible [AV, 1611].) The \u201cchargers\u201d are obviously like the one that \u201cserved up\u201d the [v_Mat_14_8] head of John the Baptist to Mrs. Herod (Matt. 14:8; Mark 6:28): it is a large, hollowed-out dish (Heb.: kots). The \u201cbasons\u201d are \u201ccovered goblets\u201d which would resemble any one of ten thousand German \u201csteins.\u201d"
